title: love the overall purpose
review: I really love the overall purpose of your company! Having a young independent artist myself, for them to he able to share their work and get paid for it is amazing! I also am very pleased with the quality of the sweatshirts! Your sizing charts need to be a little more accurate, I did measure and the size I ordered is way too big. Luckily the person it was for loves big fitting clothes! Your communication with customers about shipping could be a little more frequent. I had to check myself more than once. Also maybe make it a little bigger and bolder that it is 6 - 8 business days! Not any sooner.. My next issue which is the main reason for this review is, for the price of 2 sweatshirts and shipping it cost me $80. Ok, no problem there. My problem is what they were shopped in! Just a plastic mailer. No protection between the shirts and the plastic. The shirts were just folded up and stuffed in a mailer bag. There were 2 big rips in the bag, exposing the sweatshirts! Luckily there was no damage to them!I would expect way better quality in the shipping packaging for the price I paid!

title: Great Designs / Quality Control Issues/Great Customer Service
review: UPDATE 11/29/21: After contacting customers service they were very quick to rectify the issues I had. I appreciate the quick and thorough job they did once I contacted them.______________Placed a very large order ($180.00), weeks went by, got a shipping confirmation but never went anywhere when checked. I contacted customers service, they were great, redid, resent order. I got second order in a normal time, but they printed the front design of one of the shirts on the back. The day after got the replacement order the original order showed up with the wrong shirts (things I did not order inside) things I ordered missing and same shirt with image printed on the back again. To be fair, I just couldn't even bother to deal with customer service again. They may have fixed the problem, but I just have had enough after waiting over a month for it all. It was/is frustrating. Between the two orders I still don't have one complete order of my original choice of shirts.The artwork and selection from the artists is great, the printing and shipping, not so great. Two stars for the selection options.

title: Thank you for the opportunity for feedback!
review: I really appreciate the opportunity to review your product.I couldn't find any links on the site to directly contact the seller/designer, nor found any direct link in my email until this.Unfortunately, I was disappointed with the result of the shirt.it's not of high quality. the reds are not completely saturated and show more orange in hue. the transfer is speckled, suggesting either a print issue, a transfer material quality issue, or perhaps an overheat.and sometimes this is desirable for a vintage look.But i recall the image on the website being solid in color and not advertising or warning against this effect.Unfortunately, it appears that the daftpunk logo listing has been removed from Teepublic.Also, it appears alot of the offerings from the designer/seller "Borntobechild" are do longer available (they come up in the teepublic search, but link to "something similar".Additionally, the quality of the shirt is very average. Its a Gildan shirt that you'd get at michaels for $3.Its rough cotton with large collar edge, classic 90s.Again, i wanted to confirm if I just missed this in the listing, but the listing can no longer be found.I can't even seem to find a link from the emails.price and shipping time. you got that going for ya. but honestly, not worth it if the quality was this poor.i'm currently left with a shirt that i'm embarrased to gift.As a reference, I've been making shirts with iron-ons and screens since 1998. i've been purchasing from zazzle and other tshirt sites since 2010ish.i'd like to hear your reaction to this feedback and how we can improve the quality of the product and overall experience for the future.

title: Ordered a bunch of shirts to ship to myï¿½ï¿½ï¿½

The package supposedly shipped on the 5th of December. I then asked for assistance and was told they would not help me until after Christmas. I personally feel like this is a Scam Site and do not or will not ever recommend using this site.Ordered on Dec 2, 2022 at 1:24 ESTShipping InfoStandard (6-9 Business Days)-- $9.99Shipped Dec 5, 2022 @ 8:12 ESTDavid TI am sorry to hear this. Given that the delivery is Guaranteed before Christmas, the package should arrive by the end of the day on the 24th, even if it is delayed on the way to USPS.As I have previously mentioned, in the unlikely event your order doesn't reach you by Christmas, please let us know so that we can make this right for you.

title: Terrible Quality and Poor Customer Service too!
review: I had ordered T-Shirts through TeePublic before and never had an issue which is why this time around I decided to order a few designs that I had ordered before as I loved them so much as well as some new ones.I ordered a total of x8 T-Shirts totaling a cost of just under ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½198.01 and not one of them is up to their usual standard?The T-shirt Quality and colours are really poor, the navy tees look like they had already been washed twenty times before it was delivered and all of the prints on every T-Shirt are either blurred, patchy or are dull in colour in comparison to what I have ordered from them before.The higher quality versions of the T-Shirts used to have the Teepublic logo printed in the back of the shirt but the new t-shirts have a"Gilden" written in them and whoever these guys are they are ruining the quality of the products and Teepublic's reputation.Attached are a number of images showing the defective products, the first shows two of the same design in navy, the one on the left is the original TeePublic shirt, the one on the right is the one I have just purchased with the Gilden label and as you will see the t-shirt colour looks faded and despite being a brand new print the design looks dull in comparison to my old tee that has been washed numerous times?The rest of the pics highlight the poor print of the rest of the new tees.I really hope I can exchange these for the same designs but to the usual standard of TeePublic that I love and hope is still around but I'm now concerned that others have said they never receive a response to their request for refund or replacement.Please also note, I have a Galaxy S20 phone that automatically focuses on images and makes them more vibrant, but trust me, these look MUCH worse in reality.So disappointed as I genuinely loved buying off these guys.Also customer service is non-existent, they don't respond to emails.

So i contacted customer service and the same thing we'll send you the 3 missing shirts. Next day (yesterday) I got 2 more packages, 1 medium size and 1 small again like the first. title: A Love/Minor Hate Relationshipï¿½ï¿½ï¿½
review: I have a love/minor hate relationship with TeePublic, all depending on the quality of the shirt and the transfer.Some shirts I get have images that remain intact and unblemished even after numerous washings.Other shirts have a transfer so obvious in its lesser quality that I know from the outset that the image will start to chip, peel, and fade after only one or two washings.I have appreciated the prompt delivery, the eclectic selection, and helpful customer service.I am amazed at how many of my interests are represented in not one but, often, several designs.Overall, I like the company.I like the easy-to-navigate website.I like the surprised and delighted reactions I get from others.When that happens, I always give TeePublic an advertisement and a recommendation.I just wish the quality was more consistent from shirt to shirt.

title: Great looking products, delayed international delivery, BUT excellent post-sale customer service
review: There are two elements to service for an online order - the ordering process (i.e. the website) and the delivery.The ordering process was great - really good website.However, I placed my order on 3rd July using international delivery which is supposed to be 10-15 days. The items actually arrived on 27th July. For all I know this may be the fault of UPS (their online tracking certainly suggests that the package just sat in the same place for days on end). Either way, it was a very disappointing service and undermined the products as they were ordered as a birthday gift. UPDATE to original review: TeePublic contacted me immediately after I posted this review, apologised for the delay (even though it might have been UPS's fault), and refunded the cost of delivery. Excellent customer service that should be recognised and applauded.

title: Seller and Buyer deserve Better
review: I am both buyer and seller of this order. While everything was eventually settled (sort of), I did not receive what I ordered by the deadline. The tees were meant to be for a specific event which I could not postpone. One package arrived damaged and late, with shirts missing. Two of the shirts had misprints. One package did not arrive at all. One of the misprinted shirts was allegedly the fault of the file, yet no communication about the file being "bad" happened and it conformed to the posted file specs on the website. When the replacement package finally arrived, one shirt was sized too small for the recipient, and there was yet another misprint-- neither of which I care to ask for a replacement or refund. I had intended to switch to Teepublic after many years of (more expensive) success with Neat-O-Shop. Looks like I will not be switching after all and will continue to shop your competitors.

title: Maybe Worth the Hassle?
review: **Update #2** I received replies to my initial review and the first update. The first said they aren't "big like Amazon" and can't change/negotiate with shippers; bullsh*t on two fronts.One, Amazon doesn't negotiate since they are the third largest shipper of US packages--they dropped FedEx because they passed them. So don't compare to Amazon. Second, you only negotiate to save costs on your end, not the consumer's, since you still charge for shipping. I'm not asking for cheaper shipping, just better options, say the USPS who would have had my priorty package here in three days for the same/slightly lower price UPS charges to get it here in two weeks! Hell, I'd pay a few bucks more to have a USPS delivery option, since they're not as inept as UPS/FedEx. And before you reply again TeePublic, USPS picks up packages, so zero excuses.I was also told in the first reply to contact about my shipping issue. Problem is the reply came 48 hours after receiving a confirmation that my email (regarding shipping issue) was received.I then received a reply to my first update to contact about the quality issues, saying to mention the review in my contact, which I did. This time, magically I got a response within 24 hours. They (rightfully) refunded my shipping charge, and had replacements sent. Sending an email stating: "We're so sorry that your order has taken this long to be processed by the third-party fulfiller. In an effort to get this to you ASAP, we have upgraded your order to the highest priority level." That was a week ago. Still no replacements. Granted the package has been delayed by two days now in FedEx custody-not directly Teepublic's fault. However, it took 48+ hours from the email I received issuing the replacement order to when the package was given to FedEx (ground!). None of that screams "highest priority level," especially when the initial order shipped (in carrier's hand) with 24 hours of being placed.We are now over three weeks since my initial order and I still don't have half of it! Will update again when I receive the replacement, however, this is and will always be a 1-star experience. Teepublic has done nothing to change that.**Update** Finally got my order, 3 business days and a weekend later. Of the five shirts I ordered, two were acceptable. One was printed off-center and crooked, AGAIN! The other two were either incorrectly tagged or just lacking QC, as all five shirts were the same style and size, but these two are THREE inches shorter than the others (not the first time I've had this issue either).Teepublic's incessant need to ship using UPS mail innovating makes it real hard to like them; but REAL EASY to chargeback my order. I've placed close to a dozen orders and every single time my order arrives days to weeks after it should.Currently my order (6 to 8 days) is on it's 10th business day of sitting in the UPS system. If I have to pay for shipping and it doesn't arrive when stated then you're going to get chargedback or lose a customer.That all being said, the quality of the shirts themselves has always been acceptable; the printing on the other hand is generally atrocious. Haven't had a single order without issue: off-centered printing, ink bleed, image rotation. But Teepublic is always quick to fix the issue and reprint the shirts. Would just be easier/more economical to do it correct the first time, but that happens when you don't have you're own in-house printing.Nearly a dozen orders and everyone shipped from a different location. That happens when you use third-party printers--I get it--but it also means the shirts you receive are different every time. Even reprints aren't the same brand/style, since they ship from another shop.Bottom line: you get what you pay for...eventually. If you need an item in a hurry, look elsewhere, otherwise be patient, I guess.

title: Good Products, Good Service
review: Reviewing all of TeePublic is not what this is meant to be, rather, just the service and the products I received from TeePublic. I purchased 3 masks with different designs on them, and I'm very satisfied with the products I received. The shipping time was longer than I would have liked however I'm certain had I dealt with TeePublic before COVID-19 was causing a pandemic the shipping time would have been faster. No fault on their end.The products themselves are well made - they fit pretty well and the design is clear. I have not washed them a satisfactory number of times to report how well they hold up in the wash.If I had any constructive criticism it's that the whole piece of fabric should be dyed black first before stitching. When you pull the main piece of the fabric (gently) away from the seams of the elastic, you can see that it's white underneath. I don't need to be pulling it to notice it necessarily, either. I would say to whoever would buy from TeePublic not to let that deter you from buying masks. It's not a big enough issue to offset how good the mask is overall.At the end of it, 5 stars. This has been my only experience with TeePublic thus far, and it very well may not be the last. If I need a good T-Shirt, I'll probably look here first. Thank you, TeePublic!

I mentioned this in the first review and at the same time noted that there was another design of the model 3 that I would like to get and give you guys a second chance.I followed up and bought that shirt with that design and again was dissatisfied with the quality of the print.I was wondering, what will it take 2 own and proudly wear a really nice shirt with a high quality print?I'm thinking, that I guess I would be willing to pay $100 for a really great shirt with my dream car model 3 until I own that vehicle.To me, you guys have some great ideas but the quality of the product is not good enough.I guess I would have tweeted Facebook and possibly Instagram you guys if I was really amazed with your product; however that's not going to happen at this time.Thanks for hearing me out,Tien

review: I'm so glad I was invited to share a review.After uploading my original design that is my company logo that I am the sole owner and creator of, I ordered a couple items from my store to ensure quality before presenting the option to my fans. Shortly after the order was placed, I was notified that I had somehow violated their terms with the image that I uploaded and my account, which included access to my upload, was terminated. I attempted, repeatedly, to contact them about it for an explanation as I had reviewed the terms and found nothing that I may have violated. Teepublic refused to respond to my request, and when I attempt to login, it says this account is not active, so I tried to open an account on the same email address and it says the email is in use. Pretty scummy customer service, since you asked me.

review: The customer service team are brilliant, the issue is that it feels like the business model simply doesnt work. They have brilliant designs, but then send them to 'local' printers (my understanding). The first Tee I received was so poor quality print, and the explanation was that the printer couldn't achieve the design! This is not good enough considering the long lead times - why would a printer actually take the job on and send it out to a customer if they knew it was poor?? I was offered a replacement design (unsure if same printer printed it) but it was not great -not sharp, not punchy, all the ink sort of split as the fabric spread. Neither Tee really suitable to wear out - very disappointed.

title: Great Service, Average Quality Control
review: The ordering process was simple and when I had an issue with the quality of one of the garments the employees were helpful and quick to replace the item. Even though for some reason I couldn't get the same design reprinted it was nice to have the option to have another design printed without the need to return the damaged sweatshirt.Some attention to improving quality control could be helpful. I noticed that the print tends to have a stickiness to it until it's washed and when the vendors folded the garments they fold the print towards itself so it got stuck to itself resulting in the sticky print peeling itself off when opening up the sweatshirt. I bet there'd be less returns if the garments are folded backwards so that the print doesn't touch itself. If possible creating some sort of barrier between multiple items or putting each item into it's own bag or something could help reduce the risk that different items could stick to each other.Overall, from ordering to customer service, it was a pretty smooth process.

title: $30 bucks for this???
review: So, my first thoughts on the product were not good. I have pics but do not see where I can attach!The art on the front and back is what I sent in, however, it seems like it was not printed with care.The front "B THE EFFECT" print looks like it was stretched while getting printed. A bit of unintended distortion. The back print has stripes like when a printer is running low on ink. (Kind of when you print at home, it prints side to side.) These stripe marks is exactly what I saw first when opening the package. The brand marks below the art are blurry and unreadable.The quality of the shirt is so-so. Itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s a very thin and light, Canvas brand shirt. Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d expected a higher quality shirt. Something substantial, thick.The package is another small thingï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ It was a cheap plastic mailer with no extra padding nor paper receipt. Many businesses send the invoice receipt (or a business card or promo flyer, something) in with the item. IMO, not the best QA here.Honestly, paying $28 for this is not worth it for lack of printing quality. I repeat, the art is great. The printer sucked. You donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t place a masterpiece in a $5 frame! This is disrespehing they believed would be loved, to only have it fall so below standards.All in all, a refund would be only part of the solution. Printing (and shipping) needs to be given some serious attention. If you really care about the art community and the people that make it what it is, show that care through the product.

title: Classic logo, nicely done.

I went on a train ride on Northern Pacific when I was three years old, and that logo stuck in my memory, much like the awesome Vista-Dome car I fell asleep in while looking up at the stars while my mom covered me in a blanket and smooched my cheek. title: I have ordered here before the pastï¿½ï¿½ï¿½
review: I have ordered here before the past Holiday and there's no way I would have allowed myself to pay the insane shipping rates that have changed from then to now. It's not only charging me seperate shipping for each item I selected, but 5-7 day ground shipping for $13.99! Are you freaking kidding me? This is multiplied by however many items you are buying.I thought that maybe I could add a few more gifts and it would ship them all together, so if I spent more money in bulk, I would save on shipping total as a smaller percent of my total price.... Nope. 1 Womans Tshirt, $16 + $14 shipping and 1 Hardcover Notebook for $15 + $14 shipping. That's $31 worth of actual goods and $28 worth of shipping for the slowest 5-7 day shipping which should be around $4-$5 range maximum and items should be combined into a single order.The fact they have multiple warehouses set up to do simple things like manufacture a shirt or print a pattern on a notebook and you choose to pass these expenses on to your customers isn't a good look in my opinion. I won't be paying making this purchase as after tax and shipping is calculated I would be spending about 45% of the total on the items themselves, and 55% on taxes and shipping. Unreasonable and I'm not sure why any American would support this robbery. Shipping did not rise THAT much although I'm well aware of inflation, 300-400% increase for shipping on your site in a single year is insane TeePublic on top of splitting items up and charging shipping per item instead of 1 bulk order. The products are great quality and last a decent amount of time but by the time you checkout the cart on your $15 meme shirt you've spent $50 and could have just bought designer and supported local business instead.I would have been willing to pay $7.99 to ship both items total, not $28 for 2 lightweight, tiny items, when you're a few states away in all your warehouses from NY. I'm tight on money from HODLing Doge and Moon stocks I'd rather buy another share of AMC than just blow $28 on shipping into the void.

title: TeePublic's quality has just plummetedï¿½ï¿½ï¿½
review: TeePublic's quality has just plummeted in the past couple years.Used to be very happy to get shirts from them, and this year has just been bad.The shirts they are using now don't reflect the true size.If the shirt says it's a medium, it's going to actually be a small or XS.I ordered both female and male shirts, and they were all way smaller than the tag.Had them redo a sweater because the Large I ordered, which usually fit loose for me, I couldn't even get it on.It was ridiculously tiny.Trying to be smart I asked them to print one on a 2XL... the 2XL fits like a medium-large.If I was actually someone that needed a 2XL, like some in my family, I wouldn't even be able to attempt to get this on my body.On top of that, this time the picture is printed way off, crooked, and skewed.Maybe they're outsourcing the printing now, maybe they are using cheaper stuff to print, but it's NOT working. I'm honestly afraid to order stuff from them again.You have no idea what size you are really getting, no matter what the tags on the shirt say.It doesn't even make sense.I can imagine there's going to be a lot of gifts that people just won't ever wear or they are going to be getting a lot of emails for fixing things this year.

title: I love the designs and am sad that some designs stick to themselves
review: I love the designs, like the light shirt weight as we live in Texas. I have ordered about eight shirts from TeePublic. I've bought both full-screen and more open designs and like both. I am disappointed that your full-screen designs tend to stick to themselves. I wash all my clothes in cold water on permanent press cycle and never put them in the dryer (really!). I have had to gently separate one section of the shirt front from the other side, or try to shake the shirt front straight before laying it flat to dry. Twice, one part of the design has stuck to itself enough to pull the design "ink" off and leave it on the other sticking point. This has not happened with the more "open" designs. I guess I'll order the open screen designs in the future.

title: Brilliant designs wasted on sloppy shoddy work!
review: Taking forever to receive everything I ordered. Still have not received the last shipment. Spent over $200 and have been waiting a month. Shirts I did receive are the poorest quality printing. I've basically accepted that the images will disappear within one to two washes. Ordered two of the same design, same type of shirt, same color, image printed on shirts were grossly different sizes. The one looks normal while the other appears almost comically small to the point when wearing it you have no idea what it is unless you take a long look at it. I've done screen printing myself in the past and know what is involved in the process. This is just sloppy, rushed work with no regard for quality whatsoever. It is truly shameful that these great designs are being translated into subpar work. These artists deserve better, and so do your customers!

title: tee shirts for your bodhi
review: I like my tee shirts to come from a place way off the grid.I want them to be unique references to obscure pop culture. There is just one company that I know of that is up to the task.I have made numerous orders through teepublic.com and the company has earned my trust because of its attention to detail and quality. It gives timely updates on the status of my orders, and it has a large selection of colors in its tee shirt inventory.But the best part of its working relationships with independent artists is the mind-boggling variety of designs they come up with.It's got to be ofgeometric proportions; I don't know if you could even search the entirety of it.My approach is to enter specific information into the search field, such as a B-movie horror film from the 80s, and it comes back with pages and pages of designs every time. Teepublic.com has elevated itself to promoting and selling cultura, defined as the refinement and deeper knowledge of pop culture.The company's "where did you get that?" tag line is a subtle acknowledgment of people like me who are fans of cultura.

title: GOAT MASKS- POSTAL DELAY
review: GOAT MASKS- POSTAL-The goat masks we received was of excellent quality.The grand children loved the goat masks!But i went with standard shipping 10-15 days. thinking i would get the masks in the designated shipping time, but DID NOT get the masks until 3 days later of shipping time. So our grandchildren did not get to use them for the purpose of having them for (4-H GOAT JUDGING) I would of paid for 2-3 shipping if I would of known this was gonna be a problem. Ihad a grace period of 1 week for the masks to arrive before judging, but looking at the tracking of order i saw they were sent out fine, but laid at several different Post Offices for a couple of days, while they could of been sent out. I understand the COVID -19 crisis with shipping, but your company should not guarantee standard shipping when the order is not going to arrive within the 10-15 days stated.. .The Grand children are wearing the masks to school and for everyday, and have received several compliments on them, even though they DID NOT have themfor 4-H!! THANK YOU!.

Then they post an embedded message that it will be redelivered the next business day. Just more complicated than it should be. Also, I really like the "tagless" aspect of the t-shirts, but there are remnants of the old tag still sewn into the collar, which could be scratchy.

title: Using Covid-19 is not an excuse for poor CS
review: Using Covid-19 is not an excuse for poor customer service. While we understand that delays have been occurring on getting merchandise shipped, the lack of communication around such shipping issues was more concerning. After an initial email that said the order was received, it took them more than a month before they finally acknowledged that they had a problem with my order, and only after I reached out to them to ask where the order was. If the company knew that such issues were occurring, they should have done a better job at pro-actively notifying customers and allowing them to seek alternatives. Instead, an order that was meant to be a birthday gift was not delivered on time, disappointing my son.

title: The order arrived somewhat more timelyï¿½ï¿½ï¿½
review: The order arrived somewhat more timely than in past occasions I have ordered from Teespring, however the quality of the actual print is terrible. I ordered a classic hoodie and a lightweight hoodie, both of which are of the quality that I expected if not better, but the actual image that was printed on them looked unsaturated, like a printer with barely enough ink to finish the job. Additionally, on the classic hoodie that I ordered, the logo overlaps onto the seam of the front pouch of the hoodie. This could have been easily fixed if the image had just been resized or even moved up a bit on the sweater front. One of the sweaters turned out good, lack of saturation notwithstanding and the other looks like crap. I wouldn't order this again. In the future I would actually just try to buy the image direct from the artist and have it printed locally where the quality could be better.

title: Satisfied first time customer
review: I am a first time customer and would recommend TeePublic to my family and friends because of my recent experience. I ordered my #11 Yu Darvish coffee mug on Nov 16. Product was shipped on Nov 18 and expected date of delivery was Nov 29 @ 9:00pm. At 7:00pm (Nov 29) as I was waiting for the delivery, the UPS delivery time suddenly changed to the next day (Nov 30 @ 9:00pm). While I confirmed the date and time once again at 11:00pm (Nov 29th), the UPS delivery date once again changed to Dec 10 @ 9:00pm. I quickly contacted Tee Public for an explanation as to why the delay when I paid my item to be shipped between 6-8 business days. Tee Public quickly apologized for the delay and even refunded my shipping charge. My Yu Darvish mug arrived on Dec. 08 @ 7:40am. I am a satisfied customer and will be purchasing more items in the future.

title: Ridiculously small sizes and can't contact them.
review: [Edited after TeePublic response] BE WARNED! Sizing is very misleading, tag on shirts indicates ordered size, but are very undersized. I did receive replacements but the men's XXL T-shirt from TeePublic is comparable in size to a Large Hanes brand undershirt. The only way to contact them is through their fully automated site, which can find my order and tracking information but when I go to try do a refund or size exchange, suddenly it can't find my order and won't let me proceed and there is no contact information provided by the seller. The only reason I ever got help was because I posted a very negative review warning that they are a scam seller and they contacted *me*. While I did get my order corrected, these people operate suspiciously and I strongly advise you to avoid them.

title: Don't recommend ordering
review: Hmm, where do I start. The artists designs are great, but the people that print the designs must have their worked checked by a quaility assurance department with every order! There is also a "heat stain" that appears on the printed shirts from the printing machines. The customer service messages go to several different customer service reps instead of one person to resolve the issue, which leads to mistakes. I ordered several T-shirts from Tee Public but two of the shirts were unacceptable. The first was a purple shirt with a black word printed on the shirt; the black print was sent as a purple print, which you cannot see on a purple shirt. It was indeed meant to be a black print. Customer service tried to help by reordering the shirt reprinted, but the next one came with the print crooked (not straight). I reported it a second time and they sent another to be reprinted, then contacted me back and said the shirt was no longer available in the color purple so I chose it to be printed on a heather gray color. They ended up sending a crooked printed heather gray shirt and also sent another reprinted purple shirt that finally turned out straight. The other shirt with an issue was a pink shirt I ordered. I reported it because you could see right through the shirt when wearing. Their emails and website stated to contact them for returns or exchanges, so when I reported the see-through shirt, they said they didn't do exchanges but could make a one-time exception to print the shirt on a different color...hmm. I went along with getting the shirt printed on a different color, because I paid for the T-shirt; the reprint came with crooked print that was outlined in a white colored border, which wasn't supposed to be there. I tried one more time to get the shirt I paid for because I was told by customer service that they could get it reprinted from a different processing center. The shirt came with the print too far over to the right and not centered on the shirt. I'm extremely disappointed in this company and I will never order from them again. I'm done with the incompetence of this company and will not recommend them to anyone.

title: Pretty but not protective
review: I ordered five masks, two of which were for my kids. Those did not seal at all over their noses, and were too thin (height from nose to chin) for my 7 year old. I love the graphics, but we won't likely use these masks much at all because they offer so little protection. Two of the adult masks were a thin material that I'm sure would not block small particles. They did have pockets for a filter, and I don't feel protected wearing them without one, which is a shame. The filter should be additional protection. These two were an accordion pattern, which unfortunately made the graphic text on them largely unreadable. The text was of course, why I bought them. The final adult mask seemed of a tighter weave, but still somewhat thin. It covered the face well enough but didn't seal great at the top. It's a real shame we don't have some kind of a standard measure for face mask safety, because I don't feel confident that any of these will serve the very important purpose for which they were intended. I'm happy to support independent artists, but masks are a matter of personal and public safety. There needs to be quality control in place.

title: Great design, bad logo placement
review: I love the design of the shirt I ordered, and the quality of the shirt itself is decent and standard for most offerings these days. What I don't like, and why I didn't rate 5 stars, is where the logo is placed. It literally goes directly across my breasts, and this isn't exactly the look I was going for. Logos, especially those that are of words, need to be centered over the upper chest, not directly over the breast line. Upon further inspection of the picture provided before I ordered, I now see that if I had looked more closely I would have seen the logo was further down and I wouldn't have ordered it. My fault. But I've honestly never found a shirt with a logo placed quite like this one. I was super excited to find this vintage design in the exact color I wanted, but I doubt I'll ever wear it out of the house because I don't want to wear a shirt that screams, "Hey, look at my boobs!" So, as a suggestion to the artist, please move the logo up a tad.

title: "TEEPUBLIC" Saved my Christmas
review: "TEEPUBLIC is the best place to get quality, unique, custom products and quality service,"(TeePublic)SAVED CHRISTMAS. I ordered about 10 custom shirts,almost to late. The only request they asked of me was to donate the previous order & spread the joy since it was the holiday season. TEEPUBLIC made my son,several other kids& 1GREATFULL mom so happy. TEEPUBLIC are also 1 of the only places that carry custom 3,4,5XL. Now my son can express himself and have cool unique cloths.This had nearly been impossible until I found TEEPUBLIC. Iwill only order tee-shirts, hoodies ect from TeePublic. Plus the artist are insanely talented. You will be able to find something for everyone you know. Now it's time to order some things for my self. THANK YOU SO MUCH TEEPUBLIC. YOUR CREW IS AMAZING.

title: Very thin fabric and doubtful prints
review: I've been ordering t-shirts for many years at Moteefe, Shirtcity, Speadshirt etc. Read a few bad reviews, but decided to give TeePublic a chance because of the designs.First off, pricing is excl. vat, which is very uncommon for private sales (vs b2b were it is always done), making the final total sum a very disappointing. This lead me to wait ordering. When i looked at my shopping cart the next day, suddenly prices had lowered about ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½6 per shirt (excl. vat) and brought the price to the competitors level.The order was made on and shipping was fast (3 business days).Upon receiving i noticed the bag was a little small to hold 5 t-shirts my size (XL). Opening confirmed that the t-shirts are rather thin and are see through. I ordered the tri-blend so may others types may be thicker, but not what i was expecting and seriously doubting whether they will hold up over time. Same goes for the print. Not the worse i have seen, but i can't shake the feeling the some was tr"ink". Future will tell, but for now... i don't feel like i bought a good product, maybe even feel a little cheated. For the moment, i will buy my t-shirts elsewhere until these from TeePublic have proven their worth.

title: Careful if you expect delivery by a certain date...
review: The products I received were fine and as expected. The trouble lies in the shipping. I placed an order a month before Christmas with "Guaranteed by Christmas" shipping. I know- once an item is shipped its in the hands of the delivery services, but hear me out- The items were shipped via Mail Innovations, which, if you are not familiar, is NOT a guaranteed service in any way- Mail Innovations tells companies that use their service this openly and makes it a very poor choice for a company to use for Guaranteed by any date delivery. One item arrived on time, the other got lost in Ohio for 3 weeks. When I contacted TeePublic days before Christmas,they agreed to reship the item that was lost in transit but would not guarantee Christmas delivery which was a huge disappointment since that was the purpose of the purchase in the first place. So, 3 stars for the product, but the fulfillment left a lot to be desired.

title: I love the soft shirts from Tee Public
review: I love the soft shirts from Tee Public. The quality has always been great. It's very convienent to get the design, color and size you want, and Tee Public often has a sale where shirts are discounted over 30%. I have purchased dozens of shirts from Tee Public over the years and have only had good experiences. I've read a few reviews where people claim they've gotten poor quality shirts. I always get the tri-blend, extra-soft shirts that cost a bit more but they have always been durable. Perhaps there's a difference with some of the classic tee fabrics, but my experience with the tri-blend / extra-soft tees has been nothing but positive.

title: Shirts are decent quality, but sizing is off
review: Shirts are decent quality, and the prints seem to hold up. The variety that is offered is good, although it does suck that no "copyright" words can be used, so it's a little hard to find specific things you'd be interested in buying a product of. The only main complaint that I have (and the reason for one star off) is that the sizing is off by a good amount. It said to size up when buying a shirt, but even then the shirt was smaller than expected when it arrived. It also shrunk in the wash, so now it's almost 2 sizes smaller than what I ordered, and a size smaller than what I wanted. Other than that, everything was pretty good. There's a good chance I'll buy more from here, while keeping the shirt sizing in mind.
